The paper deals with deformable image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and medical imaging. The proposed approach involves learning a metric aggregation using anatomical segmentations, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning using structured support vector machines, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning, leading to the possibility of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories. The paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM), and the proposed approach involves optimization, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
